const benefits = [
  {
    icon: '📞',
    title: 'Catches Calls During Hands-On Work',
    text: "Laying pavers, pouring resin, operating a compactor, cutting borders with a diamond blade — driveway work means hours where your phone is physically unreachable. When a call goes unanswered, Missed Call Text Back sends a branded text within seconds. The caller knows you are working and will return the call."
  },
  {
    icon: '⏱️',
    title: 'Acts Before They Call the Next Company',
    text: "A homeowner comparing driveway quotes calls three companies. Voicemail from two, a text response from one within six seconds. That text is the difference between staying in the race and being forgotten. The caller pauses their search because you acknowledged them."
  },
  {
    icon: '🏷️',
    title: 'Branded and Credible',
    text: "The text arrives from your business number with your company name. For driveway work — where homeowners spend £5,000 to £20,000 and need confidence in the contractor — a professional text response after a missed call immediately signals that you are a serious, organised business."
  },
  {
    icon: '📊',
    title: 'Safety Net During Spring and Summer Rush',
    text: "March to September is peak driveway season. Enquiry calls flood in while you are on site from 7am to 7pm. Missed Call Text Back ensures every unanswered call gats an instant acknowledgement, preventing leads from slipping away during your busiest weeks."
  },
  {
    icon: '📋',
    title: 'Captures Reply Context',
    text: "Many callers reply to the text with useful details — 'looking for a block paving driveway, about 40sqm, in Banbury' or 'need a resin driveway before Christmas.' Your lead summary includes the phone number and the reply. You call back informed."
  },
  {
    icon: '🔄',
    title: 'Backup to AI Phone Answering',
    text: "Phone answering catches the vast majority of calls. Missed Call Text Back catches the rare exceptions — a caller who hangs up after one ring, a brief signal dropout, or a moment between calls. Together, they ensure no enquiry is ever missed entirely."
  }
];

const faqs = [
  {
    question: "When does the text get sent?",
    answer: "The text fires the instant a call reaches voicemail or remains unanswered past your set ring time. The caller receives it within seconds — before they have scrolled to the next driveway company in their search results. During peak driveway season when homeowners are shopping aggressively, this immediacy keeps your name in every conversation."
  },
  {
    question: "What does the text message say?",
    answer: "You compose the message during setup and can edit it any time. A typical driveway company text might read: 'Thank you for calling [your business]. We are currently on site working on a driveway installation and will return your call as soon as we finish. Reply with your driveway requirements for a quicker response.' The tone and wording are entirely yours."
  },
  {
    question: "Does this replace the AI Phone Answering?",
    answer: "They are complementary, not interchangeable. AI Phone Answering answers the call and captures a detailed lead through conversation. Missed Call Text Back handles the small number of calls that slip past — callers who hang up before the AI picks up, or connectivity gaps. Phone answering is the main system; text back is the fallback."
  },
  {
    question: "How much does Missed Call Text Back cost?",
    answer: `This feature costs £${pricing.addOn.price}/month as an add-on. For a driveway contractor where the average domestic job exceeds £5,000 and larger projects reach £15,000 to £25,000, recovering a single missed call through a text response pays for the add-on for years. During spring and summer when enquiry volumes peak, the value multiplies.`
  },
  {
    question: "Do callers actually reply to the text?",
    answer: "Frequently. Common responses include the driveway size, material preference, current surface, postcode, and urgency. These replies appear in your lead summary alongside the missed call record, giving you a phone number, a project brief, and a location before you have even checked your voicemail."
  },
  {
    question: "Is missed call data kept private?",
    answer: "Missed call data — including phone numbers, driveway dimensions shared in text replies, property addresses, and material preferences — is encrypted end-to-end and stored on UK and EU servers governed by UK GDPR. The information is accessible only to you and is never sold, shared with marketing platforms, or repurposed in any way."
  }
];
